main event: On July 20, 1966, a civilian sighted a UFO in Rendleton, Illinois, observing it for 10 to 30 minutes before it landed and then disappeared from view.
interesting points: The object circled at about 5 degrees above the horizon while moving in an erratic manner., There were no physical evidence such as photographs or materials., The object was concluded to possibly be a balloon., The duration of the sighting was estimated to be between 10 to 30 minutes., The report is part of Project Blue Book, a historical UFO investigation program by the U.S. Air Force.
